-- Berkshire’s MidAmerican Sees Capital Spending Climbing in 2015
-- B y   N o a h   B u h a y a r
-- 2013-11-08T21:40:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-08/berkshire-s-midamerican-sees-capital-spending-climbing-in-2015.html
MidAmerican Energy Holdings Co., the
utility company controlled by  Warren Buffett ’s Berkshire
Hathaway Inc., said capital spending may climb 25 percent next
year as the business expands in Nevada through an acquisition.  MidAmerican forecast expenditures of $5.5 billion next
year, compared with $4.4 billion in 2013, according to a
presentation from the Des Moines, Iowa-based company that was
attached to a regulatory filing today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Noah Buhayar in New York at 
